cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dimensioning the 5G NR interface and analyzing the behavior of congestion probability in a network.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Poisson Line Process to model the distribution of users in a network.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with Quality of Service (QoS) evaluation and resource allocation in a network.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper discusses the forecast data traffic and cell throughput in a network.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns in a 5G network.
